<TITLE> Hot weather likely to continue </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 10 (bdnews24.com)  Tuesday morning in Dhaka was sunny; the monsoon banks of clouds pushed down to cling to the horizons. As the day advanced, absence of monsoon winds was turning the skies grey and dusty, exacerbating the heat. The met office said the day temperature might increase further. Dhaka, Chittagong, Rajshahi, Sylhet, Barisal and Khulna divisions at places may see gusty to squally winds accompanied by moderate rains to thundershowers. The highest temperature countrywide Monday was 35.6 degrees Celsius in Rajshahi and the lowest 24 degrees Celsius at Cox's Bazar. The highest Dhaka temperature Monday was 33.5 degrees Celsius and the lowest 26.4 degrees Celsius. The sun sets Tuesday at 6:50 pm and rises at 5:17 am Wednesday. bdnews24
